{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769475219,"nonce":"Ts4rjuHBrdLcDDXSGu6hpk0DD1M=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87l-UTH","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/52","origin":"github"},"title":"Standardize GitHub Issues as Source of Truth \u0026 Enforce Branch Protection","message":"## Problem\nThe workspace currently relies on a manual `.agent/ROADMAP.md` file as the \"Source of Truth\" for tasks. This has led to:\n1.  Desynchronization between actual work and documentation.\n2.  Confusion regarding issue tracking (e.g. ambiguity around the state of related issues like #45).\n3.  Agents committing directly to `main` because the workflow documentation is ambiguous about enforcement.\n\n## Goals\n1.  **Deprecate `ROADMAP.md`**: Move all active tracking to GitHub Issues/Projects.\n2.  **Enforce Workflow**: Technically prevent direct commits to `main` via pre-commit hooks.\n3.  **Update Agent Protocol**: Rewrite `WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md` to explicitly treat GitHub Issues as the authority.\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n- [ ] **Infrastructure**: Add `no-commit-to-branch` hook to `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (block `main`, `jazzy`, `rolling`).\n- [ ] **Documentation**: Mark `.agent/ROADMAP.md` as deprecated/read-only.\n- [ ] **Protocol**: Update `AGENTS.md` and `WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md` to require:\n    - Checking GitHub Issues before starting.\n    - Creating a branch named `feature/\u003cissue-number\u003e-\u003cdesc\u003e`.\n- [ ] **Cleanup**: Create actual GitHub issues for the \"High Priority\" items currently only listed in the Roadmap.","files":null}]}